Last Broadcast Date: Mon 22 Mar 2010
9/11 Compensation Former New York Fire Fighter Kenny Specht tells us how he believes his health suffered due to the toxic dust he inhaled at ground zero . Now he and his colleagues are fighting for compensation to help with their medical care. Bangladesh goes Digital Mark Dummett reports for Outlook from Bangladesh on how the internet is changing the lives of people in rural areas. Argentina's 'Living Disappeared' Victoria Donda is the youngest female deputy in the history of Argentina. A child of Argentina's "Dirty War", she was born in prison and stolen from her real mother and adopted by a military family who renamed her Analia. She has written about her experiences in a book called "My name is Victoria". Show less